SINGLETON DESIGN PATTERN :
Only one instance of a class exists throughout the application and provides a single global point od access to it.

This is used at places where resources that should exist only once: 1.DB connection manager 2. Cache manager etc.

Prevents accidental creation of multiple instances and ensures controlled, effiecient use of resources like memory and connections.

Features:
1.Single instance.
2.Global access point: Provides centralized way to acesss the instance.
3.Lazy or eager initialization: An instance can be created at class load time (eager) or when first needed(lazy).
4.Thread efficiency: Can be designed to work correctly in multithreaded env.
5.Resource management: Useful for managing shared resources like configuartions, logging or DB connections.
